quran[5]{c,v,t}:
  61,10,O believers! Shall I guide you to an exchange that will save you from a painful punishment
  61,11,"˹It is to˺ have faith in God and His Messenger, and strive in the cause of God with your wealth and your lives. That is best for you, if only you knew"
  61,12,"He will forgive your sins, and admit you into Gardens under which rivers flow, and ˹house you in˺ splendid homes in the Gardens of Eternity. That is the ultimate triumph"
  61,13,"˹He will also give you˺ another favour that you long for: help from God and an imminent victory. ˹So˺ give good news ˹O Prophet˺ to the believers"
  61,14,"O believers! Stand up for God, as Jesus, son of Mary, asked the disciples, “Who will stand up with me for God?” The disciples replied, “We will stand up for God.” Then a group from the Children of Israel believed while another disbelieved. We then supported the believers against their enemies, so they prevailed"